 ball with both hands as if trying to deflate the ball.";i:6;s:38:"Hold for 4 seconds and slowly release.";i:7;s:22:"Repeat the exercise 8.";i:8;s:53:"Seated exercise classes are some of our most popular.";i:9;s:132:"The gentle chair-based exercises are great for improving your posture and balance and are suitable for people with reduced mobility.";i:10;s:82:"Some classes introduce resistance bands and hand weights for muscle strengthening.";i:11;s:201:"Exercise 4 Chair Marching First check your posture Lift alternate legs so that your feet lift about 2 inches from the floor and swing your arms forwards and back at a speed that is comfortable for you.";i:12;s:43:"Imagine you marching along at a brisk pace.";i:13;s:33:"Continue for about 20 30 seconds.";i:14;s:160:"Types of classes include Pilates Aqua Postural Stability Strength Balance and different levels of Chair-based exercises you can find a full list on the website.";i:15;s:171:"The sessions cost 370session or 10 sessions for 32 and are spread across venues in Brampton Buckden Eynesbury Huntingdon Ramsey Sawtry St Ives St Neots Warboys and Yaxley.";i:16;s:158:"This chair based exercise routine is ideal for people who are concerned about their ability to stand while exercising so we do the whole routine sitting down.";i:17;s:126:"Youll be surprised at how much you can work your whole body from a chair and this can be done in the comfort of your own home.";i:18;s:76:"Exercise Classes for Seniors in Weymouth Portland Sunshine Fitness Weymouth.";i:19;s:147:"A gentle and fun seated exercise class for those wishing to improve their physical mobility and wellbeing in a welcoming safe and friendly setting.";i:20;s:54:"Classes take place at the Emmanuel Church in Southill.";i:21;s:42:"Contact Sally Claire for more information.";i:22;s:47:"6 chair exercises in an easy 10 minute routine.";i:23;s:126:"Dartmouth-Hitchcock an East Coast health care organization created a simple 10 minute chair exercise routine for older adults.";i:24;s:123:"The only equipment thats needed is a sturdy chair with back support an optional resistance band and optional ankle weights.";i:25;s:129:"Right now Tally sees a chasm between CrossFit and BODYPUMP classes at one end of the spectrum and chair classes at the other end.";i:26;s:213:"Tally believes there is a great need for focused instructor trainingso that facilities can hire qualified and certified instructors who understand the needs of older adults and can make modifications to suit them.";i:27;s:101:"Bend your elbows bringing the dumbbells up to your shoulders while keeping your elbows by your sides.";i:28;s:66:"If you need the chair for balance while in a standing position do.";i:29;s:79:"L2 Chair-based Exercise Instructor endorsed- Live on Zoom 21 22 Sept 1030-1330.";i:30;s:38:"Virtual Training via Video Call Level.";i:31;s:37:"Accredited by a Professional Body eg.";i:32;s:27:"HSE CIEH FSA Certification.";i:33;s:23:"Seated Gentle Exercise.";i:34;s:90:"Sit and Be Fit brings easy chair exercises for seniors that strengthen both body and mind.";i:35;s:59:"Join our streaming club for 24x7 access to chair exercises.";i:36;s:93:"This workout includes fall prevention drills and exercises to improve strength and endurance.";i:37;s:55:"A chair and handheld weights or tubing are recommended.";i:38;s:49:"Find Fitness Location View Online Class Schedule.";i:39;s:69:"The updated Chair-Based Exercise course was launched in January 2013.";i:40;s:187:"The LLT CBE training course teaches exercise leaders to be knowledgeable and competent in delivering the 22 exercises that make up the evidenced based Sit Tall Stand Strong CBE Programme.";i:41;s:71:"The 4 day CBE course is designed for a range of health and social care.";i:42;s:181:"Chair-bound exercises are ideal for people with lower body injuries or disabilities those with weight problems or diabetes and frail seniors looking to reduce their risk of falling.";i:43;s:204:"Cardiovascular and flexibility chair exercises can help improve posture and reduce back pain while any chair exercise can help alleviate body sores caused by sitting in the same position for long periods.";i:44;s:134:"Exercise Classes For Seniors The exercise classes listed below are open to the public and free of charge for adults 65 years and over.";i:45;s:91:"Each class is led by a trained non-physiotherapist instructor for a duration of 30 minutes.";i:46;s:56:"Classes may include the following components of fitness.";i:47;s:53:"Cardiorespiratory exercise Range of motion Endurance.";i:48;s:266:"AllActive courses teach non-fitness professionals to encourage and lead safe and effective exercise sessions within their community school or workplaceThis unique range of short-courses has been developed by fitness training experts to inspire exercise for everyone.";i:49;s:102:"Even those who may encounter barriers to traditional exercise methods or typical fitness environments.";}}